						<summary>

						<p>On a stone set up close to the front wall of the Sōmēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>1128 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This is dated the Chālukya-Vikrama year 52, Kīlaka, Vaiśākha śu. [10], Wednesday, corresponding to 1128 A.D., April 11.</p>						

						<p>It seems to register a gift of land. The record is worn out and the details are lost. </p>						

						</summary>
